Package interfaces

Interface iWalker

  • public interface iWalker
    Interface defining navigation and walking functionalities in a game environment. This interface provides methods for obtaining the player's position, taking steps, and walking along predefined paths within the game.

    • Method Detail

      • setup

        void setup​(java.lang.String customMapfilePath)
        Configures the system to use a custom map file instead of the default worldmap. This method must be called before any operations that require map data are performed to ensure the custom map is loaded and ready for use. If a custom map is not set up using this method, the system will revert to using the default map.
        Parameters:
        customMapfilePath - The relative file path to the custom map file. Path must be relative to your script directory.

      • getPlayerPosition

        Tile getPlayerPosition()
        Gets the player's current position.
        Returns:
        Tile representing the player's current position on the map.

      • getPlayerPosition

        Tile getPlayerPosition​(RegionBox region)
        Gets the player's current position within a specified region.
        Parameters:
        region - The region for which to determine the player's position.
        Returns:
        Tile representing the player's current position within the region.

      • step

        void step​(Tile worldmapPoint,
          RegionBox region)
        Takes a step to a specified Tile. Needs to be visible on the minimap.
        Parameters:
        worldmapPoint - The tile to step to on the world map.
        region - the RegionBox region you are in on the worldmap.

      • walkPath

        java.lang.Boolean walkPath​(RegionBox region,
                           Tile[] path)
        Walks along a specified path within a given region.
        Parameters:
        region - The region within which to walk the path.
        path - An array of Tiles representing the path to walk.
        Returns:
        Boolean indicating whether the path was successfully walked.

      • walkPath

        java.lang.Boolean walkPath​(Tile[] path)
        Walks along a specified path without providing a region. This should primarily be used if using custom maps
        Parameters:
        path - An array of Tiles representing the path to walk.
        Returns:
        Boolean indicating whether the path was successfully walked.
